    '%3Cp%3EThis%20subject%20deals%20with%20the%20application%20of%20civil%20practice%20in%20New%20South%20Wales%20and%20enables%20students%20to%20understand%20the%20legal%20and%20ethical%20context%20in%20which%20lawyers%20operate%20within%20the%20civil%20jurisdiction.%20Areas%20of%20study%20follow%20the%20interpretation%20and%20application%20of%20civil%20practice%20governed%20by%20the%20%3Cem%3ECivil%20Procedure%20Act%202005%3C/em%3E%20%28NSW%29%20%28CPA%29%20and%20the%20%3Cem%3EUniform%20Civil%20Procedure%20Rules%202005%3C/em%3E%20%28NSW%29%20%28UCPR%29.%20The%20CPA%20and%20UCPR%20form%20the%20framework%20for%20case%20management%20in%20the%20Supreme%2C%20District%20and%20Local%20courts.%20The%20subject%20follows%20the%20scope%20of%20the%20CPA%20and%20UCPR%2C%20including%20the%20resolution%20and%20settlement%20of%20disputes%2C%20the%20commencement%20of%20proceedings%2C%20representation%20and%20advocacy%2C%20the%20drafting%20and%20filing%20of%20documents%2C%20service%2C%20interlocutory%20applications%20and%20resolution%2C%20including%20alternative%20processes%20for%20dispute%20resolution.%20The%20legislation%20gives%20power%20to%20judicial%20officers%20to%20direct%20the%20business%20of%20the%20court%20and%20caseload-manage%20all%20matters%2C%20and%20to%20direct%20the%20parties%20as%20to%20the%20management%20of%20their%20individual%20case.%20Statute%20is%20supported%20by%20relevant%20case%20law.%20Three%20of%20the%20significant%20results%20of%20the%20uniform%20civil%20procedure%20regime%20that%20students%20work%20with%20are%20the%3A', '%3Cul%3E%20%3Cli%3EIntroduction%20to%20civil%20procedure%20and%20guiding%20principles%20of%20civil%20procedure%20law%3C/li%3E%20%3Cli%3ECase%20management%20and%20the%20%u2018Overriding%20Purpose%u2019%20of%20the%20Civil%20Procedure%20Act%202005%20%28NSW%29%20%3C/li%3E%20%3Cli%3EAccess%20to%20justice%20and%20open%20justice%3C/li%3E%20%3Cli%3EIndigenous%20civil%20justice%3C/li%3E%20%3Cli%3EAlternative%20Dispute%20Resolution%20%3C/li%3E%20%3Cli%3EJurisdiction%20and%20limitation%20periods%3C/li%3E%20%3Cli%3EInitiating%20proceedings%20and%20commencing%20litigation%3C/li%3E%20%3Cli%3EJoining%20parties%20and%20causes%20of%20action%3C/li%3E%20%3Cli%3EDrafting%20pleadings%3C/li%3E%20%3Cli%3EService%3C/li%3E%20%3Cli%3EEvidence%20in%20proceedings%3C/li%3E%20%3Cli%3EInterlocutory%20applications%20and%20injunctions%3C/li%3E%20%3Cli%3ECosts%20and%20settlement%3C/li%3E%20%3Cli%3EStrike-out%2C%20summary%20disposal%2C%20and%20vexatious%20litigants%3C/li%3E%20%3Cli%3EEnforcing%20judgment%3C/li%3E%20%3Cli%3EAppeals%3C/li%3E%20%3C/ul%3E%20%3Cp%3E',
