    '%3Cp%3EInternational%20law%20is%20a%20well-established%20branch%20of%20law%20with%20a%20wide%20scope%20of%20application%20and%20far-reaching%20implications%20for%20States%2C%20individuals%20and%20entities.%20International%20law%20differs%20from%20other%20legal%20systems%20because%20of%20its%20horizontal%20nature%20and%20its%20distinct%20sources%20and%20subjects.%20This%20horizontal%20characteristic%20is%20based%20on%20the%20fact%20that%20States%2C%20the%20primary%20subjects%20of%20international%20law%2C%20are%20legally%20equal.%20It%20is%20States%20that%20create%20international%20law%20through%20treaty%20and%20custom%2C%20the%20principal%20source%20of%20rights%20and%20obligations.%20International%20law%20can%20thus%20be%20contrasted%20to%20domestic%20legal%20systems%2C%20in%20which%20laws%20created%20by%20a%20central%20legislature%20bind%20natural%20and%20legal%20persons%2C%20and%20where%20higher%20courts%20subordinate%20lower%20courts.', '%3Cul%3E%20%3Cli%3EIntroduction%3A%20nature%20and%20subjects%3C/li%3E%20%3Cli%3ESources%3C/li%3E%20%3Cli%3ERelationship%20between%20international%20and%20municipal%20law%3C/li%3E%20%3Cli%3EPersonality%20and%20recognition%3C/li%3E%20%3Cli%3EJurisdiction%20and%20immunities%3C/li%3E%20%3Cli%3ELaw%20of%20Treaties%3C/li%3E%20%3Cli%3EState%20responsibility%3C/li%3E%20%3Cli%3EPeaceful%20settlement%20of%20international%20disputes%3C/li%3E%20%3Cli%3EUse%20of%20force%3C/li%3E%20%3C/ul%3E%20%3Cp%3E',
