    '%3Cp%3ECorporations%20are%20an%20integral%20part%20of%20contemporary%20economies%2C%20through%20enabling%20individuals%20to%20manage%20their%20potential%20liabilities%20by%20incorporating%20business%20structures%20with%20separate%20legal%20personalities.%20As%20corporations%20may%20raise%20capital%2C%20borrow%20funds%20and%20enter%20into%20contacts%2C%20it%20is%20important%20for%20all%20law%20graduates%20to%20have%20a%20sound%20understanding%20of%20the%20key%20principles%20of%20corporate%20law.%20This%20subject%20provides%20students%20with%20a%20comprehensive%20overview%20of%20the%20key%20principles%20of%20Australian%20corporate%20law%20under%20the%20Corporations%20Act%202001%20%28Cth%29.%20It%20covers%20the%20formation%20and%20life%20cycle%20of%20Australian%20corporations%3B%20contractual%2C%20tort%20and%20criminal%20liability%3B%20corporate%20decision-making%20processes%3B%20the%20role%20of%20the%20Australian%20Securities%20and%20Investments%20Commission%20in%20regulating%20companies%2C%20financial%20markets%20and%20financial%20services%3B%20corporate%20fundraising%3B%20corporate%20governance%3B%20the%20duties%20of%20directors%20and%20officers%20and%20members%20remedies.', '%3Cul%3E%20%3Cli%3EHistorical%20development%20of%20Australian%20corporate%20law%20and%20regulation%3C/li%3E%20%3Cli%3EEthical%20and%20theoretical%20considerations%20in%20managing%20companies%3C/li%3E%20%3Cli%3ESeparate%20legal%20personality%3C/li%3E%20%3Cli%3EOther%20business%20structures%20%28including%20partnerships%29%20and%20rationale%20for%20forming%20companies%3C/li%3E%20%3Cli%3EFormation%2C%20types%20and%20life%20cycle%20of%20companies%3C/li%3E%20%3Cli%3EContractual%2C%20tort%20and%20criminal%20liability%20of%20companies%3C/li%3E%20%3Cli%3EInternal%20rules%20of%20companies%3C/li%3E%20%3Cli%3ECorporate%20authority%20and%20contracting%3C/li%3E%20%3Cli%3ECorporate%20decision-making%3C/li%3E%20%3Cli%3ERegulation%20of%20financial%20services%20and%20markets%20and%20corporate%20fundraising