    '%3Cp%3EBiotechnology%20can%20be%20defined%20as%20the%20use%20of%20biological%20systems%20%28whether%20living%20cells%20or%20cell%20components%29%20for%20the%20efficient%20manufacture%20or%20processing%20of%20products%20that%20help%20improve%20lives%20and%20the%20health%20of%20the%20planet.%20The%20biological%20processes%20of%20microorganisms%20have%20been%20exploited%20for%20thousands%20of%20years%20to%20make%20useful%20food%20products%2C%20such%20as%20bread%20and%20cheese%2C%20and%20to%20preserve%20dairy%20products.%20Modern%20biotechnology%20uses%20these%20traditional%20practices%20of%20fermentation%20for%20the%20industrial%20production%20of%20many%20compounds%20such%20as%20vaccines%2C%20hormones%2C%20antibiotics%20and%20enzymes.%20The%20genomic%20era%20has%20provided%20information%20allowing%20for%20the%20controlled%20and%20deliberate%20manipulation%20of%20genes%20for%20the%20production%20of%20recombinant%20medical%20and%20industrial%20products%20and%20in%20the%20synthesis%20of%20novel%20crops%20to%20respond%20to%20emerging%20pressures%20on%20global%20food%20supplies%20and%20for%20the%20management%20of%20pests%20and%20diseases.%20Genetic%20manipulation%20has%20also%20been%20applied%20to%20microorganisms%20used%20in%20bioremediation%20processes%20to%20enhance%20the%20removal%20of%20toxic%20contaminants%20from%20soil%20or%20groundwater.%20However%2C%20biotechnology%20is%20more%20than%20just%20innovative%20research%20and%20discovery%3B%20in%20reality%20it%20is%20a%20hybrid%20of%20business%20and%20science.%20Biotechnology%20is%20about%20translating%20research%20ideas%20into%20products%20on%20the%20market%3B%20making%20money%20out%20of%20molecules.', '%3Cp%3EThis%20subject%20is%20designed%20to%20develop%20an%20understanding%20of%20the%20biotechnology%20industry%20from%20the%20most%20fundamental%20aspects%20to%20the%20cutting%20edge%20technologies%20used%20today%2C%20with%20a%20focus%20on%20the%20major%20streams%20of%20food%2C%20medical%20and%20environmental%20bio